---------------------------------------------------------------------------
PROBLEM 1

$ ./ucm 
Altitude (km): 200
Velocity: 7784.26 m/s

SOLUTION:
      v = 7,784 m/s

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
PROBLEM 2

$ ./period 
Altitude (km): 200
Period is 5309.65s.

SOLUTION:
      P = 5,310 s

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
PROBLEM 3

$ ./georadius 
Orbital period (s): 86164
GEO radius:   4.21641e+07 m
GEO altitude: 35786 km

SOLUTION:
      r = 42,164,170 m

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
PROBLEM 4

$ ./velocity 
(Apogee) Altitude (km): 250
(Perigee) Altitude (km): 500
Velocity at perigee: 7541.82 m/s
Velocity at apogee: 7826.29 m/s

SOLUTION:
      Vp = 7,826 m/s
      Va = 7,542 m/s

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
PROBLEM 5

$ ./apogee 
Perigee altitude:
Altitude (km): 200
Velocity (m/s): 7850
Altitude at apogee: 427.003 km

SOLUTION:
      Altitude @ apogee = 6,805,140 / 1,000 - 6,378.14 = 427.0 km

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
PROBLEM 6

$ ./eccentricity 
Enter altitude at perigee.
Altitude (km): 200
Enter velocity at perigee.
Velocity (m/s): 7850
Eccentricity: 0.0169617

SOLUTION:
      e = 0.01696

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
PROBLEM 7

$ ./altitude 
Semi-major axis (km): 6700
Eccentricity: 0.01
Altitude at apogee:  388.86 km
Altitude at perigee: 254.86 km

SOLUTION:
      Altitude @ perigee = 6,633 - 6,378.14 = 254.9 km
      Altitude @ apogee = 6,767 - 6,378.14 = 388.9 km

